# Articulate 360 Integration

## description
This rule provides guidelines for integrating React Native training content with Articulate 360 for enhanced learning experiences. It helps align repository content with Articulate 360 Guide requirements.

## globs
["docs/**/*", "**/*.md", "**/*.html"]

## alwaysApply
true

## Rule Content

### Purpose
Ensure that React Native training materials can be effectively adapted for use in Articulate 360 while maintaining consistency with the repository content.

### Content Alignment
- All training content should be structured to facilitate easy migration to Articulate 360
- Markdown content should use consistent formatting that can be easily transferred
- Code examples should be self-contained and include all necessary context
- Visual aids should be high-resolution and in formats compatible with Articulate 360 (PNG, JPEG, SVG)
- Complex diagrams should have separate text explanations for accessibility

### File Naming Conventions
- Use descriptive, hyphenated names for all content files
- Include module and section numbers in filenames for easy sorting
- Avoid spaces and special characters in filenames

### Content Preparation Guidelines
- Break content into logical chunks that align with Articulate 360 slides
- Ensure all images have alt text descriptions
- Maintain a consistent voice and terminology throughout all content
- Keep paragraphs concise and focused on a single concept
- Use bullet points and numbered lists for step-by-step instructions

### Media Requirements
- Screenshots should be at least 1920x1080 resolution
- Diagrams should be in vector format when possible
- Videos should include captions and transcripts
- Audio narration scripts should be included alongside training content

### Assessment Integration
- Quizzes and knowledge checks should be designed for easy implementation in Articulate 360
- Interactive exercises should have clear instructions and expected outcomes
- Assessment questions should align directly with learning objectives

